name: Whole Wheat and Honey Pizza Dough
author: brookes
summary: Quick, easy, yummy homemade pizza dough, which you can top any way that you like.  This makes a thin crust but it can be doubled for a thick crust.
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water
Let stand until creamy, about 10 minutes
In a large bowl combine flour, wheat germ and salt
Make a well in the middle and add honey and yeast mixture
Cover and set in a warm place to rise for a few minutes
Roll dough on a floured pizza pan and poke a few holes in it with a fork
Bake in preheated oven for 5 to 10 minutes, or until desired crispiness is achieved
